<paragraph id="2418850BFFAB835BFF4859D6FDE9FD76" blockId="22.[112,765,277,909]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
As shown in other cases below, Boissier’s protologue of a given taxon was sometimes presented in a broader geographic interpretation than found on the specimens in his herbarium or other herbaria. The reverse situation was also observed. In the case of Saint (or 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFFAB835BFEE35A55FEA7FDB6" box="[295,311,565,589]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
.) 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFFAB835BFE885A55FE10FDB6" box="[332,384,565,589]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Saba</collectingCountry>
, or Mar 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFFAB835BFE1B5A55FD82FDB6" box="[479,530,565,589]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Saba</collectingCountry>
in Arabic, Wikipedia states that it is a Greek Orthodox monastery overlooking Kidron Valley to the east of Old Jerusalem City.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFFAB835BFF485AF5FE47FC76" blockId="22.[112,765,277,909]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
Greuter &amp; Burdet (
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFFAB835BFEB05AF5FD01FD56" author="GREUTER, W. &amp; T. RAUS" box="[372,657,661,685]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="79 - 99" refId="ref139260" refString="GREUTER, W. &amp; T. RAUS (ed.) (1983). Med-checklist notulae, 7. Willdenowia 13: 79 - 99." type="journal article" year="1983">GREUTER &amp; RAUS, 1983</bibRefCitation>
) reduced 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FFAB835BFFB55AD6FF4CFD36" box="[113,220,694,717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Matthiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis id="16D35919FFAB835BFFB55AD6FF4CFD36" box="[113,220,694,717]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">M. aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a subspecies of 
<emphasis id="16D35919FFAB835BFE755AD6FDC3FD36" box="[433,595,693,717]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FFAB835BFE755AD6FDDFFD36" box="[433,591,693,717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Matthiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipetala">M. longipetala</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the differences in the indumentum, presence of glands on the sepals, petal color and shape, and seed width justify the recognition of two distinct species, as done by 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFFAB835BFE055B75FDF6FCD6" author="ZOHARY, M." box="[449,614,789,813]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" refId="ref145270" refString="ZOHARY, M. (1966). Flora Palaestina 1. Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities." type="book" year="1966">ZOHARY (1966)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFFAB835BFD5F5B75FF25FCB6" author="GOWLER, Z. R." pageId="22" pageNumber="22" refId="ref139191" refString="GOWLER, Z. R. (1998). A taxonomic revision of the genus Matthiola R. Br. (Cruciferae) and related genera. PhD Thesis, University of Edinburgh." type="book" year="1998">GOWLER (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FFAB835BFF045B55FEFDFCB6" box="[192,365,821,845]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Matthiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis id="16D35919FFAB835BFF045B55FEFDFCB6" box="[192,365,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Matthiola aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFFAB835BFDCD5B55FDD3FCB6" box="[521,579,821,845]" name="Israel" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Israel</collectingCountry>
and neighboring 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFFAB835BFFB55B35FF29FC96" box="[113,185,853,877]" name="Jordan" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Jordan</collectingCountry>
, and its report from 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFFAB835BFE535B36FE53FC96" box="[407,451,854,877]" name="Iraq" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Iraq</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFFAB835BFE175B35FD56FC96" author="RECHINGER, K. H." box="[467,710,853,877]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="133 - 308" refId="ref142961" refString="RECHINGER, K. H. (ed.) (1968). Lunarieae, Alysseae, Matthioleae, Hesperideae. Fl. Iranica 57: 133 - 308." type="journal article" year="1968">RECHINGER, 1968: 240</bibRefCitation>
) was based on plants of 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FFAB835BFEF85B16FE40FC76" box="[316,464,885,909]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Matthiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipetala">
<emphasis id="16D35919FFAB835BFEF85B16FE40FC76" box="[316,464,885,909]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">M. longipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
